window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b><i>Nate Temple has holes in his soul, both imagined and real....</i></b></p> <p>And the only way to patch his soul back together is to go back to where it all began. To where he began. To where a Manling was born....</p> <p>To a dangerous boy named Wylde.&nbsp;</p> <p>Because to have any hope at standing against Mordred - to save Camelot and St. Louis alike - he must learn what it means to be a Catalyst.&nbsp;</p> <p>A little boy must know his legend - his origin. And he must learn the painful truth that his entire life has been meticulously planned and laid out like the steps to a choreographed dance. And that Mordred is just another dance card in a long line of future suitors at the Temple Ball.&nbsp;</p> <p>If Nate can survive the dance, that is....</p> <p>Letâ€™s discover what dangers a little boy can get into when his imagination is more real than reality itself....</p> <p>When the powers of life and death can be heard in the absent humming of a little boy playing in the woods with his cat....</p> <p>Because behind every Song is a Mask waiting to be born.&nbsp;</p> <p>Or destroyed....</p>"; 
